  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The propose of this study is to evaluate the feasibility and the clinical efficiency of
      feedback-controlled robotics-assisted treadmill exercise (RATE) technology for cardiovascular
      rehabilitation early after stroke. The investigators hypothesize that feedback-controlled
      RATE might be suitable and effective to improve cardiovascular fitness and functional
      carryover in non-ambulatory individuals with sub-acute stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
